list.item:
Column No. 3 should embrace all foreign merchandise exported
                                    from “bonded warehouse” duties remaining unpaid, or which,
                                    having been paid, are returnable as drawback.

Q. When was it that the English consul told you?—A. He told me
                                this after I had left the ship and had been to Caracas and returned;
                                this was in the latter part of the month of July, 1872.

Q. When you left her was the American flag flying?—A. No, sir;
                                when I left her we had no flag up. She was then down at the island
                                of Taos. There was a coal mine there.

Q. Do you know of any other matter or thing concerning the
                                Virginius or her character, that you have not stated?—A. No, sir;
                                not that I know of.

Q. How long was that after the discharge? How long after the
                                discharge did you leave to go to St. Thomas?—A. Immediately after;
                                the same day.

Q. Any inducement held out to you to make a statement?—A. No, sir;
                                no more than that I would be recompensed for the loss of my
                                time.

Q. Toward the coast or in the interior?—A. No; toward the center;
                                in the interior. Then I was made surgeon-general of the insurgent
                                army.

Q. About what time did you arrive in New York City?—A. About
                                February, 1870; the latter end of February or the first of March;
                                about that time.
